<%- include('partials/header', { title }) %>

<div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-16">
  <div class="max-w-lg mx-auto text-center">
    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-24 w-24 mx-auto text-red-500 mb-6" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
      <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z" />
    </svg>
    
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-red-400 mb-4">Error Encountered</h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 mb-8"><%= error %></p>
    
    <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-center gap-4">
      <a href="/" class="px-6 py-3 bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white rounded-md transition-colors">
        Return to Dashboard
      </a>
      <button onclick="window.history.back()" class="px-6 py-3 bg-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-600 text-white rounded-md transition-colors">
        Go Back
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="mt-16 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
    <div class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow-lg p-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-200 mb-4">FractalDNS Troubleshooting Guide</h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-300 text-sm">
        <p>
          If you're experiencing issues with FractalDNS, here are some common troubleshooting steps:
        </p>
        
        <div class="space-y-2">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-blue-400">Common Issues</h3>
          
          <div class="bg-gray-700 p-4 rounded-md">
            <h4 class="text-white font-medium mb-2">Zone File Access Issues</h4>
            <p>Make sure the zones directory exists and has the proper permissions. By default, zones are stored in the path configured in your FractalDNS configuration.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-gray-700 p-4 rounded-md">
            <h4 class="text-white font-medium mb-2">DNS Resolution Problems</h4>
            <p>Verify that the FractalDNS server is running on the correct port (default: 53) and that firewall rules allow DNS traffic.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="bg-gray-700 p-4 rounded-md">
            <h4 class="text-white font-medium mb-2">Peer Network Connectivity</h4>
            <p>Check your network configuration to ensure that peer nodes can communicate properly. The default peer sync port is 5353.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <p>
          For additional help, please refer to the 
          <a href="#" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">FractalDNS Documentation</a> or 
          <a href="#" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300">AetherCore Community</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>